author: dlr
msg: Per discussion with Max Bowsher, unbreak the ability to link
libsvn_swig_py on Solaris 10 after compiling with GCC 3.4.2 (a
follow-up to r10450).
* build/get-py-info.py
(link_options): Change final "else" block to a conditional which
checks whether sys.platform is 'cygwin' to gate addition of the
"-L/path/to/python/configdir -lpythonVER" flags to the output of
get-py-info.py --libs and --link (which influences the SWIG_PY_LINK
and SWIG_PY_LIBS Makefile variables).

author: rooneg
msg: Further touch-up work on directory handling in replay over DAV.
* subversion/libsvn_ra_dav/replay.c
(start_element): Before we conclude that we're under a path verify
that we actually matched the end of the path segment, in addition
to the name, avoiding problems where sibling directories have the
same prefix.

author: rooneg
msg: Fix the replay tests over DAV.
It's really unclear how this ever worked in my original manual testing...
* subversion/libsvn_ra_dav/replay.c
(start_element): Correct the logic for popping directories off the stack,
previously once we'd start popping dirs we'd go all the way up to the
root, which clearly isn't right.
